Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 14:45:30 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 31/35] feat(claim-gate): warn on suspect evidence refs in
 failed steering projections

Seam 1 of the 2026-07-01 pilot-wave consume-lane audit. On a fail/
reviewed-failed projection the evidence gates were skipped, so an
obligation carrying an all-zero sha256 digest or a nonexistent file:
ref passed silently (identical to an honest fail). Now each such ref
adds a NON-blocking warning finding (evidence.suspect_ref_on_failed_
projection); status stays host_reviewed_failed. Fail-closed behavior
unchanged. Seam 2 (host_blocked finding granularity) was a no-op:
host_witness.required_internal_gate_missing already names the gate.
Orchestration suite 821/821.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
